          <h3>SOLDIER HOLLOW</h3>
          <hr>
          <p>
            Soldier Hollow Golf is the newest addition to Utah’s beautiful Wasatch Mountain State Park. 
            The championship, 36-hole facility completes the year-round recreation programs at the 2002 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games venue. 
            Its layout sits at some of the highest elevations of the complex offering stunning views of the Heber Valley below. 
            The Gold Course is a typical mountain or foothills course with significant elevation change throughout the course and dramatic elevation changes within each hole. 
            The vegetation on the course mirrors the surrounding native area vegetation, scrub oaks and native mountain valley grasses.

          </p>
